President Barack Obama has declared May 21-27, 2011 as National Safe Boating Week in the United States. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of practicing safety precautions while boating, including taking boating safety courses, filing float plans, remaining aware of weather conditions, performing vessel safety checks, wearing life jackets, and avoiding alcohol use. The United States Coast Guard partners with boating organizations to raise awareness and promote responsible boating practices. The proclamation encourages Americans to learn more about safe boating practices and take advantage of boating education.